  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Live kidney transplantation is first choice for patients with end-stage kidney disease.
      Therefore, the safety and well-being of kidneys donors are highly important objectives in
      live kidney donation. Low pressure pneumoperitoneum can decrease postoperative pain and
      therefore also concomitant use of opioids.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      However low pressure pneumoperitoneum can also decrease peri-operative conditions. In this
      trial the researchers will investigate whether peri-operative conditions during low pressure
      pneumoperitoneum can be optimized by the use of deep neuromuscular block.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
